        content: "Un **arbore binar** e o structură ierarhică unde fiecare nod are maxim doi copii (stâng și drept).\n\n```c\ntypedef struct Node {\n    int data;\n    struct Node *left;   /* Copilul stang */\n    struct Node *right;  /* Copilul drept */\n} Node;\n\n/* Creare nod nou */\nNode *create_node(int value) {\n    Node *node = malloc(sizeof(Node));\n    node->data = value;\n    node->left = NULL;\n    node->right = NULL;\n    return node;\n}\n\n/* Exemplu de construire manuala:\n          10\n         /  \\\n        5    15\n       / \\     \\\n      3   7    20\n*/\nNode *root = create_node(10);\nroot->left = create_node(5);\nroot->right = create_node(15);\nroot->left->left = create_node(3);\nroot->left->right = create_node(7);\nroot->right->right = create_node(20);\n```\n\n**Terminologie:**\n- **Radacina** (root): nodul fara parinte\n- **Frunze** (leaves): noduri fara copii\n- **Inaltimea** (height): cea mai lunga cale de la radacina la frunza\n- **Nivel**: distanta de la radacina (radacina = nivel 0)"
